1 2. The board may not grant priority to an applicant based on sex, race, or religion.
2 Eligible applicant - Eligibility units.
3 1. An eligible applicant:
4 a. Is a member of a reserve component of the United States army, navy, marine
5 corps, air force, coast guard, or space force in the state;
6 b. Is enrolled as a full-time student at an institution of higher education;
7 c. Does not possess a baccalaureate degree; and
8 d. Has not received financial assistance under chapters 37 - 07.1 or 37 - 07.2 .
9 2. An individual who is discharged from a branch of the armed forces under other than
10 honorable conditions is not eligible for a scholarship under this chapter.
11 3. A recipient of the scholarship may receive a scholarship for no more than forty-eight
12 eligibility units.
13 4. For purposes of this section, twelve or more credit hours in an academic term equals:
14 a. Twelve eligibility units, if the term is a semester.
15 b. Eight eligibility units, if the term is a quarter.
16 Scholarship amounts.
17 1. Subject to legislative appropriations, the state board of higher education shall pay on
18 behalf of an eligible applicant:
19 a. An amount equal to one hundred percent of the tuition charged by the institution,
20 if an eligible applicant is enrolled at an institution of higher education under the
21 control of the state board of higher education; or
22 b. The lesser of an amount equal to:
23 (1) One hundred percent of the tuition charged by the institution; or
24 (2) The average tuition of all institutions of higher education under the control of
25 the state board of higher education.
26 2. The state board of higher education may require:
27 a. An applicant to apply for federal educational financial assistance programs,
28 including programs offered by the United States department of defense, for which
29 an applicant is eligible based on the applicant's military service.
