1 b. Other financial assistance received by a scholarship recipient be applied to
2 eligible expenses before scholarship funds awarded under this section may be
3 applied to the remaining eligible expenses of the recipient.
4 Active duty - Effects.
5 If an eligible applicant is called to active duty and as a result withdraws or otherwise fails to
6 complete courses for which scholarships have been awarded under this chapter:
7 1. The institution of higher education shall grant the individual a leave of absence from
8 the individual's education program and may not impose an academic penalty for
9 withdrawal or failure to complete courses.
10 2. If a scholarship for the courses has already been paid, the state board of higher
11 education:
12 (a) May not add the eligibility units for the term to the individual's accumulated
13 eligibility units, and the institution of higher education shall repay the scholarship
14 amount to the state; or
15 (b) Shall add the eligibility units for the term to the individual's accumulated eligibility
16 units as usual, if the institution of higher education agrees to allow the individual
17 to complete the remainder of the courses in which the individual was enrolled at
18 the time the individual was called to active duty.
19 State board of higher education - Rules.
20 The state board of higher education may adopt rules pursuant to chapter 28 - 32 necessary
21 to implement and administer this chapter.
